# 5. 伝えるために

Mafuyu: I'm back.
Mafuyu's Mother: Welcome home, Mafuyu. It must be very cold outside, no?
Mafuyu's Mother: It's supposed to snow tomorrow according to the forecast, so be sure to dress warm.
Mafuyu: Thank you, Mom. I will.
Mafuyu's Mother: Also, it must be very cold during club activities...
Mafuyu: Yes, it is since the archery range is an open-air area...
Mafuyu's Mother: I'm worried that you're going to catch a cold and miss cram school because of it...
Mafuyu's Mother: Your entrance exams are not too far off in the distance, so it may be time to reconsider whether club is worth your time.
Mafuyu: Right...
Mafuyu: I won't be able to immediately since I still have a lot to teach the younger members, but I'll start thinking about it...
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay, that's understandable.
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, also... I just brewed some tea.
Mafuyu's Mother: It should be steeped just right, so please have some, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: Oh, thank you...
Mafuyu: (This tea's supposed to be warm...)
Mafuyu: (But I don't feel warm after drinking it. Why is that?)
Mafuyu: (It's snowing so much now...)
Saki: Wow! This is so cool!
Shiho: Okay, okay, I get it. Also, don't run. It's dangerous...
Honami: Hehe. That's so cute. They're both just like Shibao.
Ichika: Yeah, like dogs playing in the snow. Well, we probably shouldn't tell them that...
Ichika: Oh, Asahina... Good morning.
Mafuyu: Good morning, Hoshino, Mochizuki. You all seem to be enjoying yourselves.
Ichika: Yes, we're all very excited about how it's snowing...
Mafuyu: Hehe. I know how you feel. Not only is snow beautiful, it's also fun to watch it fall from the sky.
Mafuyu: But be careful not to slip and fall, okay? It's supposed to snow quite a lot today.
Honami: Thank you. We'll be careful!
Saki's Voice: Ichi! Hona! Hurry!
Ichika: Be right there! Sorry, Asahina, if you'll excuse us.
Mafuyu: I should head up to class...
Classmate A: Ugh, I'm exhausted! They've been giving us way too much homework lately!
Classmate B: I know, right?! Well, Mafuyu here knows how to make short work of that...
Mafuyu: I wish. My cram school's also been giving me a lot of assignments, so I'm thinking about working on all that in the studying room today.
Classmate A: Oh, you are? Shouldn't you head home today since it's snowing? What if the trains get delayed or stopped?
Classmate B: Yeah. And the roads are gonna be all frozen and slippery by the time it's dark...
Mafuyu: Yes, that's true. Huh...?
Mafuyu: (Mom sent me a message...)
Mafuyu's Mother's Message: <Since it's snowing and you don't have cram school today, how about I give you a ride home?>
Mafuyu: (I should go home...)
Mafuyu: But I'd prefer to use the studying room. I feel like I can focus better there...
Classmate A: Are you sure? I mean, if you say so. Just be careful, okay?
Mafuyu: I will. Bye bye.
Mafuyu: <That's okay. There's something I need to ask my teacher, so I'll be using the studying room for a while.>
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (I wish it'd just keep snowing...)
Mafuyu: (Then, everything would be buried in snow. And I'd be able to stay here...forever...)
???: Asahina...
Mafuyu: Hinomori...?
Mafuyu: Can I help you? We don't have club activities today. Also, I thought you were practicing with Momoi and the others...
Shizuku: They had some schedule conflicts, and it's snowing, so we decided to call it off.
Shizuku: And... Asahina, if it's alright with you...
Shizuku: Would you like to practice shooting with me?
Mafuyu: Huh? Now...?
Shizuku: Yes, now. What do you think?
Mafuyu: But it's snowing...
Shizuku: Please... I really need to practice with you today.
Mafuyu: (It's rare for Hinomori to assert herself like this...)
Mafuyu: (... Plus, those assignments shouldn't take that long to complete...)
Mafuyu: Okay... Just for a little bit.
Shizuku: *Gasp* Thank you so much...!
Shizuku: Then, let's head over right now.
Mafuyu: Sure. Let me just grab my archery gear.
